pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Waterproof gloves; Shoes plus socks

Active_Ingredients.name: 11-Tetradecenyl Acetate
Active_Ingredients.mode_Of_Action: Disrupts mating communication between adult male and female leafrollers.

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if inhaled or absorbed through the skin. Causes moderate eye and skin irritation. Avoid breathing vapor. Avoid contact with eyes, skin or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably mouth-to-mouth if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for further treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.

Application_Info.max_product_per_acre_per_season: 150 gm combined a.i. per acre per year
Application_Info.application_Method: Place dispensers on rotating hook and attach to branches using a pole applicator, moving trailer, hydraulic manlift, or other safe means.
